## Overview

The first step is creating a declarations file, typically named styled.d.ts.

## Module Augmentation Pattern

The file should import the original module declarations from 'styled-components' and then extend the DefaultTheme interface with your custom theme properties. Here's the basic pattern:

```typescript
declare module 'styled-components' {
  export interface DefaultTheme {
    borderRadius: string;
    colors: {
      main: string;
      secondary: string;
    };
  }
}
```

## Why This is Needed

By default the interface DefaultTheme is empty so that's why we need to extend it.

## Creating Your Theme

Once you've declared the DefaultTheme interface, you can create a theme object by using the DefaultTheme type.

## Alternative Approaches

When you create the declarations file, instead of creating a new interface, you can extend the type of your actual theme object with the DefaultTheme.

This module augmentation approach enables TypeScript to provide proper type checking and autocompletion when accessing theme properties within your styled components.


